        <h2>The Undercount Problem: Structural Invisibility IS the Harm</h2>

        <h3>Why Census Data Undercounts Black Queer Men</h3>

        <p><strong>Family and community stigma:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Fear of rejection from family of origin</li>
            <li>Religious community condemnation (particularly in Black evangelical/Pentecostal churches)</li>
            <li>Cultural expectations around marriage and children</li>
            <li>Shame and internalized homophobia</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Structural factors:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Hostile environment immigration policies creating fear of disclosure</li>
            <li>Employment discrimination (particularly in sectors with high Black male employment)</li>
            <li>Housing instability and fear of homelessness if disclosed</li>
            <li>Police/criminal justice contact creating surveillance anxiety</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>The "down low" phenomenon:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Men who have sex with men but maintain public heterosexual identity</li>
            <li>May be married to women, have children</li>
            <li>Engage in same-sex activity privately but would never disclose on census</li>
            <li>Not captured in any official statistics</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How Much Undercount?</h3>

        <p>Research on disclosure rates suggests:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Best case:</strong> Census captures ~75% of actual LGB population (25% undercount)</li>
            <li><strong>Likely case:</strong> Census captures ~60-70% of actual LGB population (30-40% undercount)</li>
            <li><strong>Worst case (for stigmatized communities):</strong> Census captures ~50% (50% undercount)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>For Black queer men specifically, given intersecting marginalization, <strong>we estimate 30-50% undercount</strong> is most realistic.</p>

        <p><strong>This means if census shows 35,000, actual population is likely 45,000-70,000.</strong></p>

